{
  "doc_id": "32493",
  "text": "Whole tissue samples were taken from colonic glands with thickness value of 5 m which is stained using Haematoxylin and Eosin (H & E) stains. Images were captured by a charge coupled device (CCD) camera integrated with a liquid crystal tunable filter (LCTF) in the optical microscopy system [CITATION_1] . LCTF provides multispectral images of the tissue samples by changing the wavelength operation [CITATION_2] . LCTF has a bandwidth of 5 nm, and its wavelength is controllable through the visible spectrum range of 400-720 nm. Multispectral images are produced through repeated image capture in various wavelengths subbands. Moreover, the impact of multispectral imaging has been shown that the classifier accuracy increases with the number of spectral bands [CITATION_3] . Note that each image band is 8 bits coded and hence has 255 possible light intensity levels.",
